Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are promising, sustainable and efficient electrochemical energy conversion devices.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The dense and thin interlayer prepared at low sintering temperature is essential to avoid detrimental reaction between cobalt-containing cathode and zirconia-containing electrolyte.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The co-doping of transition metal ion and Gd3+ in ceria is an available new method to reduce the densification temperature, while have a negative effect on the electrical performance.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, a strategy of micro-doping for bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_delta (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers is proposed to achieve excellent sintering performance and electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that adequate liquid phase production and lattice doping could simultaneously increase the relative density at lower sintering temperature and improving the electrical conductivity of interlayers.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: 1 mol.% Cu micro-doping could reduce the sintering temperature by 350 degrees C, make the relative density up to be 96.26%, and the electrical conductivity of 600 degrees C up to be 0.0134 S/cm.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell with Ce0.9Gd0.09Cu0.01O2_delta (GCDC) interlayer has the low ohmic resistance of 0.31 omega cm2, and exhibits a high maximum power density of 0.745 W cm_2 at 750 degrees C, which was higher than 0.603 W cm_2 of the single cell with undoped GDC interlayer.
Titulo: Bifunctional Ce0.9Gd0.09M0.01O2_δ (M = Fe, Cu) interlayers with micro-doping for high-performance solid oxide fuel cells
